{
  "text": "Knowledge-based: Familiarity, Characteristicbased: Perceived similarity, Institution-based: Structural assurances, Personalitybased: Trust propensity, Trust in members (Integrity/ benevolence, Ability), Trust in website/vendor (Ability, Integrity, Benevolence), Intention to get information, Triple dimensions of trusting the seller/ web from ability, honesty and benevolence Purchase intention. [CITATION_1] A trust-based consumer decisionmaking model in electronic Commerce Perceived risk, consumer trust, perceived benefit, intention of purchase, purchase.",
